headline: How Q3 Results and Institutional Buying at Domino's (DPZ) Have Changed Its Investment Story
summary: Domino's Pizza, Inc. recently declared a US$1.74 per share quarterly dividend payable on December 26, 2025, and reported third quarter 2025 results with revenue of US$1.15 billion and net income of US$139.32 million. An increase in institutional buying, including a higher stake from Berkshire Hathaway, has underscored renewed market confidence in Domino's operational performance and growth outlook.
